| # | Finding | Severity | Location |
|---|---------|----------|----------|
| F1 | **OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler accepts `alg=none` JWTs** — any client can forge any principal name | Critical (if deployed in production) | `OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler`, `OAuthBearerUnsecuredJws` |
| F2 | **PLAIN over SASL_PLAINTEXT** exposes plaintext passwords to network observers | High (configuration risk) | `PlainSaslServer`, broker config |
| F3 | **SaslHandshakeResponse leaks enabled mechanisms** to unauthenticated clients | Low / Info | `SaslServerAuthenticator.handleHandshakeRequest()` |
| F4 | **GSSAPI ignores requested authorizationId** — always uses authenticationID | Design / Low | `SaslServerCallbackHandler.handleAuthorizeCallback()` |
| F5 | **OAuthBearer authzid/principal mismatch message exposes both values** to the client | Low | `OAuthBearerSaslServer.process()` |
| F6 | **Default `Authorizer.authorizeByResourceType()`** is O(n) over all ACLs without caching | Performance / Low | `Authorizer.authorizeByResourceType()` default impl |
| F7 | **Super-user bypasses DENY ACLs** — no way to deny a super-user | Design | `StandardAuthorizerData.authorize()` |
| F8 | **`Utils.isEqualConstantTime()` leaks password length** via early exit on `second.length == 0` | Very Low | `Utils.isEqualConstantTime()` |
| F9 | **JAAS blocklist is system-property-controlled** — can be cleared by a JVM argument | Defence-in-depth | `JaasContext.throwIfLoginModuleIsNotAllowed()` |
| F10 | **`tokenAuthenticated` excluded from `KafkaPrincipal.equals()`** — token-auth sessions and password-auth sessions are indistinguishable via equals | Design / Low | `KafkaPrincipal.equals()` |

### Positive Security Controls Observed

| Control | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Constant-time password comparison (PLAIN) | `Utils.isEqualConstantTime()` |
| Constant-time proof comparison (SCRAM) | `MessageDigest.isEqual()` in `verifyClientProof()` |
| SCRAM minimum iteration count enforcement | `ScramSaslServer.evaluateResponse()` |
| SCRAM nonce replay prevention | `clientFinalMessage.nonce()` vs `serverFirstMessage.nonce()` |
| SCRAM server never stores plaintext password | `ScramCredential` (storedKey + serverKey only) |
| API key whitelist during unauthenticated handshake | `handleKafkaRequest()` |
| Mechanism allowlist check | `handleHandshakeRequest()` |
| SASL frame size limit (512 KB default) | `NetworkReceive` + `saslAuthRequestMaxReceiveSize` |
| Principal immutability during re-authentication | `ensurePrincipalUnchanged()` |
| Mechanism immutability during re-authentication | `saslMechanismUnchanged()` |
| Generic error messages for credential failures | `SaslServerAuthenticator.handleSaslToken()` |
| AuthzId ≠ AuthcId rejection (PLAIN, SCRAM, OAUTHBEARER) | All three `evaluateResponse()` implementations |
| JNDI/LDAP login module blocklist | `JaasContext.throwIfLoginModuleIsNotAllowed()` |
| Super-user not loaded until metadata is available | `StandardAuthorizerData.loadingComplete` |

